## Previous Steps:

We are tasked with finding the minimal number of generators, \( \mu(mA_m) \), of the module \( mA_m \), where \( m = (\bar{x} - 1, \bar{y} - 1) \) and \( A = \mathbb{C}[x,y]/(x^3-y^2) \). The strategy is to find the dimension of \(mA_m\) as a \(\mathbb{C}\)-vector space, starting with the dimension of \(A_m\).

## Next Step:

Compute the Jacobian matrix of \(f(x,y) = x-1\) and \(g(x,y) = y-1\) modulo \(x^3-y^2\). The Jacobian matrix is:
\[
J = \begin{pmatrix}
\frac{\partial f}{\partial x} & \frac{\partial f}{\partial y} \\
\frac{\partial g}{\partial x} & \frac{\partial g}{\partial y}
\end{pmatrix}
= \begin{pmatrix}
1 & 0 \\
0 & 1
\end{pmatrix}
\]
